orld, in his view, also began in the decisions made by countless men and women regarding their families and circumstances. Levine ends his story with the cataclysm unleashed by the Black Death in 1348, which brought three centuries of growth to a grim end.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCivilization, Medieval. 0aHuman bodyxSocial aspectsxHistory. 0aSocial historyyMedieval, 500-1500. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aagriculture.  ablack death.  acapitalism.  aclass.  acommerce.  acommercial routines.  aearly modernization.  aeurope.  aeuropean history.  afeudalism.  agregorian reformation.  ahistory.  ainformation technology.  amaterial culture.  amodern world.  amodernity.  aplague.  apopulation density.  apoverty.  asocial change.  asocial history.  asocial order.  asocial science.  asociology.  aurban life.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052022058440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092367640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520923676423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520923676/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY